"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-spain-germany-2024-paris-olympics-womens-soccer-bronze-medal-match-live-stream-lineups-preview\", \"text\": \"In the venue that houses one of the world's most successful women's football clubs, the reigning World Cup champions square off against Germany in Friday's bronze medal match at the 2024 Paris Olympics.  This is not a consolation match, like the one at the World Cup is. These two European powers are fighting for the chance to stand on an Olympic podium. Sure, it's not gold, but to be among the top three at this ultra-competitive tournament's conclusion is something both nations can be immensely proud of.  Spain came here as the favorite despite having no Olympic experience whatsoever. After escaping one South American outfit in the quarterfinal, the second CONMEBOL side in this competition managedto get the best of it.A significant factor in the defeat was the errors made while attempting to play out from the back, which directly led to Brazil's first and fourth goals. You'd expect a team with so much technical quality and experience in big moments not to hand-wrap two goals to the opposition.  It was just the second time, dating back to the 2023 World Cup, that the Spanish had conceded four or more goals in 90 minutes.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe keep fighting for something super nice and it will continue to be the Olympics until the end,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Spain's Hermoso said. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cA bronze medal is also very difficult to get.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Germany, under the leadership of a national team legend, Horst Hrubesch, is aiming to bring home the country's fourth bronze medal in women's football. The 2016 gold medalists hold the record for the most bronze medals in women's Olympic football, with three. DFB-Frauen achieved this by finishing third in three consecutive Olympics from 2000 to 2008.  Hrubesch's teambattled Emma Hayes' USWNTfor 120 minutes without three of its most impactful players \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 captain Alexandra Popp, Lea Sch\\u00c3\\u00bcller, and Lena Oberdorf. Ann-Katrin Berger, arguably the best goalkeeper at these Games, was once again a rock between the posts. Just days after making two clutch saves and scoring the winning penalty in a shootout victory over Canada, the NJ/NY Gotham FC goalkeeper delivered another stellar performance with nine saves.  Like Lorena's crucial role for Brazil in the semifinal, her performance will be pivotal in Germany's quest for the bronze medal.  The last competitive encounter between these two sides was in the group stages of the 2022 European Championship. Popp and Klara B\\u00c3\\u00bchl scored two first-half goals in what would be Germany's second of four clean sheets in the tournament.  Goalkeeper:Cata CollDefenders:Ona Batlle, Oihane Hern\\u00c3\\u00a1ndez, Laia Aleixandri, Irene Paredes (C)Midfielders:Aitana Bonmat\\u00c3\\u00ad, Alexia Putellas, Patricia GuijarroForwards:Salma Paralluelo, Mariona Caldentey, Luc\\u00c3\\u00ada Garc\\u00c3\\u00ada  Goalkeeper:Ann-Katrin BergerDefenders:Giulia Gwinn (C), Felicitas Rauch, Marina Hegering, Kathrin HendrichMidfielders:Elisa Sen\\u00c3\\u009f, Sjoeke N\\u00c3\\u00bcsken, Janina Minge, Klara B\\u00c3\\u00bchlForwards:Jule Brand, Laura Freigang  Date:Friday, Aug. 10Start time:\\u00c2\\u00a09:00 a.m. ETLocation:\\u00c2\\u00a0Lyon, FranceStadium:\\u00c2\\u00a0Parc Olympique LyonnaisTV Info:\\u00c2\\u00a0USA Network | TelemundoLive Stream:\\u00c2\\u00a0Peacock |\\u00c2FuboTV  Score Prediction:\\u00c2\\u00a0Spain 3-1 Germany  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026Minute Media-All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Minute Media or its affiliates and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"